  "body": "A kubernetes StorageClass has a default relaimPolicy value of `Delete`. I would like to set the value to `Retain` however rook appears to ignore this attribute. In the [documentation](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/storage/persistent-volumes/#reclaiming) the allowable values are `Delete`, `Recycle`, `Retain`.  My rook setup closely follows the [quickstart](https://rook.io/docs/rook/master/kubernetes.html).\r\n\r\n```\r\napiVersion: rook.io/v1alpha1\r\nkind: Pool\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: replicapool\r\n  namespace: rook\r\nspec:\r\n  replicated:\r\n    size: 2\r\n  failureDomain: osd\r\n---\r\napiVersion: storage.k8s.io/v1\r\nkind: StorageClass\r\nmetadata:\r\n   name: rook-slow-retain\r\nprovisioner: rook.io/block\r\nreclaimPolicy: Retain\r\nparameters:\r\n  pool: replicapool\r\n```\r\n![screenshot-2017-11-26 storage classes - kubernetes dashboard](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1740337/33244959-29750fb2-d2cf-11e7-8b28-a852309ccdbb.png)\r\n\r\n![screenshot-2017-11-26 persistent volumes - kubernetes dashboard](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1740337/33244957-1dfd47d0-d2cf-11e7-8d3e-7e63bcbc3101.png)\r\n",
